</taxonomicName>
is unmistakable due to the unique, almost completely orange-red coloration of the body with strongly contrasting, black abdominal tergites 1–4. So far, this species is only known from the male 
<typeStatus box="[151,253,187,213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
